Vigilantes of the Cosmos

**Team Members:** Jack Boland, Cassandra Boland

**How would you pitch your game in one line?**
Sidescrolling space shooter with RPG elements inspired by Ikaruga, Black Paradox, etc.

**What is the key mechanic(s) that make it fun?**
Co-op, RPG Ship Customization, Dead or Alive System

**How does the game actually play? (Core Game Loop)**
Players will defeat enemies that are stationed over planets, and fight a boss at the end of certain planets
When players lower the bosses health enough, they will be able to ram the ship and launch themselves into the enemy ship where they can arrest the boss for extra rewards
Players then can enter a shopping phase and customize their ships weapons, armor, powerups, and more.
They can then move to a planet of their choosing while being able to observe the upcoming challenges and enemies

**How will you keep players engaged for 30 minutes? What's the general scope of your game (will change as you go)?**
The starting level will include all of the core features, the player will begin on a rundown ship and be able to use the
boarding feature to commandeer the ship for themselves. This will teach them all of the base mechanics and then move into a shop phase.

---
*Remember: Focus on gameplay mechanics and player experience. Save the details about story, art style, sound design, UI flowcharts, marketing plans, or achievements for later.*
